This paper proposes a method for learning skills without a reward function, which is a common problem in reinforcement learning. The paper focuses on simulated robotic tasks, which suggests a focus on robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV). The method involves maximizing an information theoretic objective, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the challenges of exploration and data efficiency in reinforcement learning, which suggests a focus on systems and control (cs.SY). Overall, the most likely categories are cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.RO, with cs.CV and cs.SY as slightly less likely possibilities.
